## 🧠 What I Learnt – Detailed Reflections from the Hands-On Work

- Real-time visibility completely changes how you think about defence. Seeing my own pentest attacks light up the dashboard made the value of logging and correlation crystal clear.
- Agent deployment on mixed OS environments is trickier than expected but incredibly rewarding once everything reports centrally.
- Writing custom rules forces you to understand attacker behaviour at a deeper level — this is exactly the analytical skill needed in operational cyber roles.
- The speed of detection reinforced why Defence invests heavily in monitoring tools; a few seconds can mean the difference between a contained incident and a major breach.
- Documenting while building (screenshots during live attacks) produced much higher quality evidence than trying to recreate it later.

This project has given me practical experience I can confidently talk about when discussing threat detection capabilities in any ADF context.

